products.productDescription: Lemongrass, also known as Cymbopogon, is a perennial grass native to tropical regions, prized for its aromatic and culinary uses. With its long, slender stalks and vibrant green color, lemongrass adds a refreshing citrusy flavor and fragrance to a variety of dishes and beverages. It is commonly used in Asian cuisine, particularly Thai and Vietnamese dishes, imparting a unique and tangy essence. In addition to its culinary applications, lemongrass is also used for its medicinal properties, as it is believed to have anti-inflammatory, antimicrobial, and antioxidant effects. Its essential oil is used in aromatherapy for its calming and soothing qualities

Rosemary (Rosmarinus officinalis) is an aromatic herb known for its delightful fragrance and culinary versatility. This perennial evergreen shrub features needle-like, dark green leaves and produces small, blue or purple flowers. It is native to the Mediterranean region but is cultivated and enjoyed worldwide.

The Sapota plant, also known as Chikoo or Sapodilla (Manilkara zapota), is a tropical evergreen tree that belongs to the Sapotaceae family. Native to Central America, it is now cultivated in various tropical and subtropical regions around the world.The Sapota tree can grow up to 20 meters in height and has a dense, round canopy of glossy green leaves. The fruit it produces, known as Sapota or Chikoo, is oval or round in shape, with a rough brownish skin that becomes softer when ripe. The flesh of the fruit is sweet and creamy, with a grainy texture similar to a pear. It is often described as having a caramel-like flavor, making it a popular choice for desserts, milkshakes, and ice creams.

The Shami plant  commonly known as jand or khejri, is a deep-rooted, perennial, multipurpose plant that is used to provide fodder for cattle in the drier areas of India and the Arabian Peninsula. Its bark is also ground up to make flour and is used during famines. It also has a plethora of ethnomedicinal benefits and commercial uses as well.
